verses.roman:
ei tina tṛṣṇā mora nahila pūraṇa
vijātīya-bhāve nahe tāhā āsvādana

synonyms: ei—these; tina—three; tṛṣṇā—desires; mora—My; nahila—were not; pūraṇa—satisfied; vijātīya—of the opposite partner of a relationship; bhāve—in ecstasy; nahe—is not possible; tāhā—that; āsvādana—tasting.
translation: "But these three desires have not been satisfied, for one cannot enjoy them in a contrary position.
